column1: Paragraph 212 of the 3.5 GHz Report and Order states:
"...for purposes of the Citizens Broadband Radio Service, rural area will be defined as any census tract which is not located within, or overlapping:
(i) a city, town, or incorporated area that has a population of greater than 20,000 inhabitants;
or (ii) an urbanized area contiguous and adjacent to a city or town that has a population of greater than 50,000 inhabitants."
The list below contains census tracts that meet this definition.
